
Overview of noun spy

The noun spy has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                            
1. (3) spy, undercover agent -- ((military) a secret agent hired by a state to obtain information about its enemies or by a business to obtain industrial secrets from competitors)
2. spy -- (a secret watcher; someone who secretly watches other people; "my spies tell me that you had a good time last night")

Overview of verb spy

The verb spy has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                            
1. (2) descry, spot, espy, spy -- (catch sight of)
2. (2) spy, stag, snoop, sleuth -- (watch, observe, or inquire secretly)
3. spy, sight -- (catch sight of; to perceive with the eyes; "he caught sight of the king's men coming over the ridge")
4. spy -- (secretly collect sensitive or classified information; engage in espionage; "spy for the Russians")
